cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the optimization problem associated with training neural networks, specifically ReLU neural networks. The paper discusses the occurrence of spurious local minima in these networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also conducts experiments related to computer vision (cs.CV) and provides a theoretical analysis of the problem (cs.SI, Symbolic Computation and Algebraic Manipulation).
